              <title></title>
              <graphic infoEntityIdent="ICN-S1000DBIKE-AAA-DA00000-A-06RT9-00091-A-001-01" />
            </figure>
            <para>As noted previously, a bike's wheels are complex devices that are composed of several components. Individually, none of these components can operate as intended. Each is dependant on one or more of the others.
						</para>
            <para>Working from the center outward there is the hub, which is comprised of the axle, bearings, and hub shell. Extending from the hub shell are the spokes. The spokes attach to the wheel rim where they are threaded to the rim through the spoke nipples. Lining the exterior of the rim is the tube. To complete the assembly, the tire surrounds the tube. Together, these components make it possible to transport the bike's rider from one place to another.</para>
            <para>Now that you have completed this topic, you should be able to identify a bike's wheel components.</para>
          </description>
        </lcSummary>
      </learningSummary>
